commit.message:
Merge pull request #19 from kbrock/recent_travis

Passing tests for recent versions of ruby
fixed encoding issues as per terotil's pull request on origin
Trying to get travis build working, using kbrocks work on original cardmagic/simple-rss
Fixed Ruby warnings about missing indentations

move development dependencies to gem spec

- explicitly require test-unit
- dont require rspec (not used)

Remove use of deprecated RubyGems #has_rdoc method

As of RubyGems 1.7.0, the #has_rdoc= method is deprecated:

  http://blog.segment7.net/2011/04/01/rubygems-1-7-0

Prior to this commit, requiring the simple-rss gem or running rake for
the simple-rss gem would produce the following warning:

  NOTE: Gem::Specification#has_rdoc= is deprecated with no replacement. It
  will be removed on or after 2011-10-01.
travis for recent versions of ruby
